# 🏎️ PIT STOP AI
### Race Through Any Webpage

> Paste a URL. Let the AI pit crew do the work.

Built at **CODE Quantum Hackathon 2026** · F1 Red Theme · Powered by Groq + Llama 3

---

## 🚀 What It Does

1. **Paste any public URL** — articles, docs, cybersecurity updates, Wikipedia, anything
2. **Watch the F1 race animation** while the AI analyzes the page
3. **Get instant structured output:**
   - 📋 **Table of Contents** — click any section to ask the AI about it
   - 📝 **Summary** — structured overview with key themes
   - 🃏 **Flashcards** — FRONT/BACK study cards, both sides visible
4. **Chat with the AI** about anything on the page
   - Quick buttons: Key Points, Flashcards, Quick Summary, Takeaways
   - **Quiz Me** — shows questions first, answers hidden behind "🏁 Show Answers"

---

## ⚡ Quick Start

**No install needed.** Just open `index.html` in your browser.

1. Get a **free** API key at [console.groq.com](https://console.groq.com/keys) — no credit card required
2. Open `index.html` (or use VS Code → Live Server for auto-reload)
3. Paste your Groq API key into the gold field
4. Paste any public URL and hit **▶ LAUNCH**

> Your API key stays in memory only — never stored anywhere. Closing or refreshing the tab clears it completely.

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Tech | Why |
|---|---|---|
| Frontend | Vanilla HTML/CSS/JS | Zero dependencies, runs anywhere, no build step |
| AI — Analysis | Llama 3.3 70B via Groq | High reasoning for structured data extraction |
| AI — Chat | Llama 3.1 8B Instant via Groq | 3-5x higher throughput for fast interactive Q&A |
| Inference | Groq LPU (Language Processing Unit) | Near-zero latency — fits the F1 "no lag" speed theme |
| Page Fetching | CORS Proxy chain | Bypasses browser CORS restrictions for arbitrary URLs |
| Text Extraction | Browser DOMParser | Native HTML parsing, no library needed |

**Single file. No build step. No backend. No npm. Just open and go.**

---

## 🏁 Features

- 🎨 F1 racing aesthetic — carbon fiber background, Ferrari red accents, tire corners
- 🏎️ Custom gas nozzle cursor (red → neon gold on hover → F1 car on click)
- 🏎️ Animated F1 car loading screen during page analysis
- 🃏 FRONT/BACK flashcards — both sides always visible for studying
- ❓ Quiz Me mode — questions shown first, answers revealed on demand
- 💬 AI chat with full page context
- ⚡ Quick-action buttons for common study tasks
- 📱 Responsive — works on mobile

---

## 🔑 Why the API Key is Needed

The API key is like the key to the F1 car — without it the engine won't start. It does three things:

1. **Verifies you're not malicious** — prevents bots from flooding Groq's servers
2. **Tracks usage** — Groq monitors your token quota even on the free tier
3. **Identifies your account** — ties the session to your specific settings

The key is grabbed directly from the input field right before each API call and placed in the `Authorization` header. It's never written to `localStorage`, never logged, and never sent anywhere except `api.groq.com`. Close the tab and it's gone.

---

## 🌐 Known Limitations

- Some sites block CORS proxies — try a different URL if it fails (Wikipedia always works)
- JavaScript-rendered sites (React/Angular apps) may return empty content — their text is injected after page load, which CORS proxies can't capture
- Groq free tier has token limits — very large pages may hit rate limits
- No conversation history — the AI doesn't remember previous messages in the chat

