## 🔮 Future Plans

This repository is a skeleton. The long-term goal is a version where:

- **No API key needed** — a backend server will hold the key server-side so
  anyone can use it without signing up for anything
- **No data saved** — sessions stay stateless by design, nothing written to a
  database or localStorage. You're still responsible for taking your own notes —
  thats intentional, it keeps you accountable for what you learned!
- **JS-rendered pages supported** — a headless browser (Puppeteer) on the
  backend will handle React/Angular sites that CORS proxies can't read
- **PDF upload** — drag and drop a paper or textbook chapter
- **Conversation history** — AI remembers previous messages in the same session  maybe make a login but no email will be need and ill put "avoid using your username and password" for the sake of databreaches not affecting ur data

The current version requires a Groq API key because the browser calls the AI
directly. The future version flips that — the server calls the AI, users just
use the app.

